comment: LHH shows that Towns (MIN) maintains legal guarding position and cleanly blocks Teague's (ATL) shot attempt.
RHH shows that Horford (ATL) does not extend his forearm into Rubio (MIN) as he attempts to retrieve the rebound.
Korver (ATL) deflects the ball away from Prince (MIN) and causes it to go OOB.
The ball crosses the midcourt line before 8 seconds elapses.
Wiggins (MIN) keeps his pivot foot down at the start of his drive.
Bazemore (ATL) does not affect Wiggins' (MIN) RSBQ at the start of his drive.
Bazemore (ATL) makes contact with Wiggins' (MIN) arm during the jump shot.
LHH shows that Rubio (MIN) maintains legal guarding position and contact is initiated by Teague (ATL) on his drive.
Wiggins (MIN) and Bazemore (ATL) briefly engage and separate prior to the inbound pass.
Rubio (MIN) maintains legal guarding position as he defends Teague's (ATL) drive.
Towns (MIN) makes contact with the ball prior to the incidental arm contact on the play to the basket by Teague (ATL).
Teague (ATL) attempts to commit a take foul on Bjelica (MIN).
Teague (ATL) makes contact with Bjelica (MIN) after the rebound. The contact is being reviewed by Basketball Operations.
Wiggins (MIN) makes contact with Millsap (ATL) with his leg during the release of his jump shot but the contact is incidental.
Wiggins (MIN) maintains legal guarding position as Bazemore (ATL) brings the ball up the court.
Rubio (MIN) establishes legal guarding position and is firming up when he absorbs the contact from Bazemore (ATL) on the drive.
Rubio (MIN) cleanly strips the ball from Teague (ATL).
Teague (ATL) makes contact to Rubio's (MIN) body that affects his RSBQ.
Horford (ATL) sets the screen on Prince (MIN) without giving him the opportunity to avoid the contact.
Horford (ATL) clamps Towns' (MIN) arm during rebounding and affects his ability to secure the rebound.
